title.narrative: 4.2. EARLY CHILDHOOD DEVT & INTERVENTION

description.narrative: 4.2. Increased national capacity to plan, coordinate, monitor and provide inclusive early childhood care practices, with a focus on neonate and children with developmental delays and disabilities, which contributes to Building Capacity For Evaluation, Child Health, Cross-Sectoral Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses, Evaluation And Research, Health Systems Strengthening, Maternal And Newborn Health. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: 4. Health & Nutrition - Improved quality maternal and child health and nutrition services and care practices
